The widow of Boston Marathon bombing suspect Tamerlan Tsarnaev has retained legal counsel who has an extensive client roster of suspected and convicted terrorists.

Katherine Russell added attorney Joshua Dratel to her legal team,
 her Rhode Island-based lawyer Amato DeLuca said on Wednesday.

The New York lawyer, whose office in Downtown Manhattan is just blocks away from Ground Zero, previously defended Guantanamo Bay detainees and suspects in the bombings of the U.S. embassies in East Africa.

